quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  103,1,"By the time!"
  103,2,"Lo! Man is in a state of loss;"
  103,3,"save those who have faith and do righteous deeds, and counsel each other to hold on to truth and counsel each other to be steadfast.",footnotes:182834:1
  104,1,"Woe to every fault-finding backbiter;",footnotes:182835:1
  104,2,"who amasses wealth and counts it over and again.",footnotes:182836:1
  104,3,"He thinks that his wealth will immortalise him forever.",footnotes:182837:1
  104,4,"Nay, he shall be thrown into the Crusher.",footnotes:182838:1,footnotes:182839:2
  104,5,"And what do you know what the Crusher is?"
  104,6,"It is the Fire kindled by Allah,",footnotes:182840:1
  104,7,"the Fire that shall rise to the hearts (of criminals).",footnotes:182841:1
  104,8,"Verily it will close in upon them,",footnotes:182842:1
  104,9,"in outstretched columns.",footnotes:182843:1
  105,1,"Have you not seen how your Lord dealt with the people of the elephants?",footnotes:182844:1,footnotes:182845:2
  105,2,"Did He not bring their plan to naught?",footnotes:182846:1,footnotes:182847:2
  105,3,"And He sent against them swarms of birds",footnotes:182848:1
  105,4,"which smote them with stones of baked clay,",footnotes:182849:1
  105,5,"and made them like straw eaten up (by cattle).",footnotes:182850:1